CHIKUNGUNYA (57): CARIBBEAN
***************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 26 Dec 2013
Source: Le Point Epidemiologie No. 3, 2013 (accessible through Institut de Veille Sanitarie, 27 Dec 2013) [in French, transl. Roland Hubner, summ., edited]
http://www.invs.sante.fr/Publications-et-outils/Points-epidemiologiques/Tous-les-numeros/Antilles-Guyane/2013/Situation-epidemiologique-du-chikungunya-dans-les-Antilles.-Point-au-26-decembre-2013


[A summary of current numbers of chikungunya virus infections confirmed by the National Reference Centre for Arboviruses (IRBA, Marseille, France), probable and suspected cases by island. - Mod.TY]

- St Martin: 66 confirmed, 14 probable, 167 suspected [with a good map of the geographic location of cases on the island - Mod.TY];
- St Barthelemy: 11 suspected;
- Guadeloupe: 1 confirmed, 21 suspected;
- Martinique: 3 confirmed, 27 suspected;
- Guyana: 1 confirmed (ex Martinique), no number given of suspected

--
Communicated by:
Roland Hubner
Superior Health Council
Brussels
Belgium
<roland.hubner@sante.belgique.be>

[There is also one confirmed case on the Dutch side of St Martin (St Maarten) Island (http://news.caribseek.com/index.php/caribbean-islands-news/sint-maarten-news/item/70422-ministry-of-public-health-reports-one-confirmed-case-of-chikungunya).

One cannot help but wonder if there will be a continuation of chikungunya virus transmission on the affected islands above, and if the virus will spread to other localities where vector mosquitoes (_Aedes aegypti_) are abundant, as travelers move about during the current holiday season.

ProMED-mail thanks Roland Hubner for sending in the above reports.

Maps showing the location of St Martin/St Maarten can be accessed at http://goo.gl/maps/TN1DJ and at http://healthmap.org/r/4zbR; Guadeloupe island at http://healthmap.org/r/9CFw; Martinique at http://healthmap.org/r/3EpV; and St. Barthelemy at http://www.caribbean-direct.com/St-Barth-Direct/Maps/STBmapsM.html. - Mod.TY]
